album.title: Please Excuse Me for Being Antisocial

wiki.summary: In “High Fashion,” Roddy Ricch uses a smooth, laid-back delivery to list an extensive inventory of luxury status symbols. Though he insists he “ain’t no player,” he also brags that he has a collection of women, and hopes that displaying his wealth in this way will persuade the object of the song to join it as his “Prada Bae.” The song is the 11th track on Roddy’s debut album and his second collaboration with Mustard, after his feature on June, 2019’s “Ballin'.” Read more on Last.fm.
